26/02/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano, who leads the ruling Socialist Party (SP), has invited the main opposition Democratic Party (DP) for talks on possible co-operation. Nano said Wednesday (25 February) that SP and DP should sign a stability pact on Euro-Atlantic integration so the country can implement necessary reforms. The statement follows a call from the head of OSCE Presence in Albania, Osmo Lipponen, for the two sides to join efforts to bolster the integration process.
In other news, Albania and Italy signed an infrastructure project agreement Wednesday. It involves a loan to fund construction of the Lushnje-Fier and Fier-Vlore road segments of the Corridor 8 project. (ATA - 25/02/04)
